_":411,"rend":406},"τὴ","καὶ",{"_":414,"hi":415},"μήρ",{"_":416,"rend":406},"τη",{"_":418,"g":419,"lb":420},"τέ κνῳ",{"_":379,"ref":380},{"n":421,"break":400},"6","γλυκυτάτῳ","ἐποίησαν",{"type":425,"name":426},"attested",[427,428],"Κασσία","Βενοῦστα",[430,433,436],{"_":431,"value":432},"ἔνδεκα","11",{"_":434,"value":435},"θ","9",{"_":437,"value":438},"η","8",{"type":440,"resp":349,"listApp":441},"apparatus",{"app":442},[443,445],{"note":444},"Text based on photographs",{"loc":446,"note":447},"line 5","Kaibel saw an ivy leaf at the end of the line, but it rather seems to be a triangle-shaped interpunct.",{"type":449,"xml:lang":122,"resp":349,"p":450},"translation","To the underworld spirits. Kassia Benousta, lived for 11 years, 9 months, and 8 days. Her father and mother made this for their sweetest child.",{"type":449,"xml:lang":286,"resp":349,"p":452},"Agli Dei inferi. Kassia Benousta visse 11 anni, 9 mesi e 8 giorni. Suo padre e sua madre realizzarono questo per la loro dolce figlia.",{"type":454,"resp":349,"p":455},"commentary",{"_":456,"foreign":457,"ref":465},"The structure of the epitaph is the most frequent in pagan epitaphs, with the invocation to the underworld spirits, the name of the deceased in the nominative form, his/her age, the name of the dedicants (in this case, the parents) and the dedication verb in aorist (Korhonen 2004: 85-86). An interesting linguistic detail is the indication of months and days in the nominative and not in the accusative form (), which seems to be due to confusion with Latin where the nominative and accusative plural of  and  correspond: for a similar confusion, see also SEG 44.0762 = . On the name , see SEG 29.931-3 (from Morgantina, 1st century CE). Note too the spelling out of the first numeral in full, rather than using the standard alphabetic notation.",[458,460,462,464],{"_":459,"xml:lang":106},"μῆνες, ἡμέρες",{"_":461,"xml:lang":290},"mensis",{"_":463,"xml:lang":290},"dies",{"_":428,"xml:lang":106},{"_":466,"target":467},"ISic000641","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000641",{"type":469,"listBibl":470},"bibliography",[471,499],{"type":365,"bibl":472},[473,484,492,215],{"type":474,"n":475,"citedRange":476,"ptr":480,"ref":482},"corpus","IG",{"ref":477},{"_":478,"target":479},"14.0483","https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760",{"target":481},"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/Q2SBPG9F",{"_":483,"target":483},"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072",{"author":485,"date":486,"citedRange":487,"ptr":488,"ref":490},"Spuches","1864","13 no.3",{"target":489},"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/NBACXKXQ",{"_":491,"target":491},"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002042",{"type":474,"n":493,"citedRange":494,"ptr":495,"ref":497},"IMusCatania","67",{"target":496},"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/2EUC82DH",{"_":498,"target":498},"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028",{"type":500,"bibl":501},"discussion",{"type":474,"n":493,"citedRange":502,"ptr":503,"ref":504},"85-86",{"target":496},{"_":498,"target":498},[506],{"n":355,"url":93,"height":356,"width":357,"desc":94,"surfaceType":352},{"title":508,"body":509,"divs":510,"images":526},"ISic001306. Epitaph for Kassia Benousta","  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001306_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic001306_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001306.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic001306-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"edition\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div\">\u003Ca id=\"al1\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>ΘΚ\u003Cbr id=\"al2\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>ΚΑΣΣΙΑΒΕΝΟΥΣΤΑΕ\u003Cbr id=\"al3\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>ΖΗΣΕΝΕΤΗΕΝΔΕΚΑ´\u003Cbr id=\"al4\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>Μ\u003Cspan class=\"petraeligature\" title=\"Ligature: these characters are joined\">Η͡Ν͡Ε\u003C/span>ΣΘ´ΗΜΕΡΕΣΗ´\u003Cbr id=\"al5\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>ΠΑ\u003Cspan class=\"petraeligature\" title=\"Ligature: these characters are joined\">Τ͡Η\u003C/span>ΡΚΑΙΜΗ\u003Cspan class=\"petraeligature\" title=\"Ligature: these characters are joined\">Τ͡Η\u003C/span>ΡΤΕ- \u003Cbr id=\"al6\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>ΚΝΩΓΛΥΚΥΤΑΤΩΕΠΟΙΗΣΑΝ\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text based on photographs\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 5\">line.5: \u003Cspan>Kaibel saw an ivy leaf at the end of the line, but it rather seems to be a triangle-shaped interpunct.\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>To the underworld spirits. Kassia Benousta, lived for 11 years, 9 months, and 8 days. Her father and mother made this for their sweetest child.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>Italian translation\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Agli Dei inferi. Kassia Benousta visse 11 anni, 9 mesi e 8 giorni. Suo padre e sua madre realizzarono questo per la loro dolce figlia.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>The structure of the epitaph is the most frequent in pagan epitaphs, with the invocation to the underworld spirits, the name of the deceased in the nominative form, his/her age, the name of the dedicants (in this case, the parents) and the dedication verb in aorist (Korhonen 2004: 85-86). An interesting linguistic detail is the indication of months and days in the nominative and not in the accusative form (\u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">μῆνες, ἡμέρες\u003C/span>), which seems to be due to confusion with Latin where the nominative and accusative plural of \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"la\">mensis\u003C/span> and \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"la\">dies\u003C/span> correspond: for a similar confusion, see also SEG 44.0762 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000641\" target=\"_blank\">ISic000641\u003C/a>. On the name \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Βενοῦστα\u003C/span>, see SEG 29.931-3 (from Morgantina, 1st century CE). Note too the spelling out of the first numeral in full, rather than using the standard alphabetic notation.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>  \u003Cli>  \u003Ca href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">14.0483\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> Spuches 1864 13 no.3 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002042\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002042\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> 67 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli>  \u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>  \u003Cli> 85-86 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. \u003C/div>",[511,513,515,517,519,521,523],{"id":365,"html":512},"\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div\">\u003Ca id=\"al1\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>ΘΚ\u003Cbr id=\"al2\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>ΚΑΣΣΙΑΒΕΝΟΥΣΤΑΕ\u003Cbr id=\"al3\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>ΖΗΣΕΝΕΤΗΕΝΔΕΚΑ´\u003Cbr id=\"al4\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>Μ\u003Cspan class=\"petraeligature\" title=\"Ligature: these characters are joined\">Η͡Ν͡Ε\u003C/span>ΣΘ´ΗΜΕΡΕΣΗ´\u003Cbr id=\"al5\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>ΠΑ\u003Cspan class=\"petraeligature\" title=\"Ligature: these characters are joined\">Τ͡Η\u003C/span>ΡΚΑΙΜΗ\u003Cspan class=\"petraeligature\" title=\"Ligature: these characters are joined\">Τ͡Η\u003C/span>ΡΤΕ- \u003Cbr id=\"al6\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>ΚΝΩΓΛΥΚΥΤΑΤΩΕΠΟΙΗΣΑΝ\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"id":440,"html":514},"\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text based on photographs\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 5\">line.5: \u003Cspan>Kaibel saw an ivy leaf at the end of the line, but it rather seems to be a triangle-shaped interpunct.\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>",{"id":449,"html":516},"\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>To the underworld spirits. Kassia Benousta, lived for 11 years, 9 months, and 8 days. Her father and mother made this for their sweetest child.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":449,"html":518},"\u003Ch2>Italian translation\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Agli Dei inferi. Kassia Benousta visse 11 anni, 9 mesi e 8 giorni. Suo padre e sua madre realizzarono questo per la loro dolce figlia.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":454,"html":520},"\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>The structure of the epitaph is the most frequent in pagan epitaphs, with the invocation to the underworld spirits, the name of the deceased in the nominative form, his/her age, the name of the dedicants (in this case, the parents) and the dedication verb in aorist (Korhonen 2004: 85-86). An interesting linguistic detail is the indication of months and days in the nominative and not in the accusative form (\u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">μῆνες, ἡμέρες\u003C/span>), which seems to be due to confusion with Latin where the nominative and accusative plural of \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"la\">mensis\u003C/span> and \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"la\">dies\u003C/span> correspond: for a similar confusion, see also SEG 44.0762 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000641\" target=\"_blank\">ISic000641\u003C/a>. On the name \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Βενοῦστα\u003C/span>, see SEG 29.931-3 (from Morgantina, 1st century CE). Note too the spelling out of the first numeral in full, rather than using the standard alphabetic notation.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":469,"html":522},"\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>  \u003Cli>  \u003Ca href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">14.0483\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> Spuches 1864 13 no.3 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002042\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002042\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> 67 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli>  \u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>  \u003Cli> 85-86 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003C/ul>  ",{"id":524,"html":525},"license"," Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. ",[527,529],{"image":93,"thumb":528,"title":94},"ISic001306_tiled-thumb.tif",{"image":360,"thumb":530,"title":94},"ISic001306-thumb.jpg"],"uses":{"params":["slug"]}}]}
